Remix of http://Wikipedia.org/wiki/Barriers_to_entry :

Barriers to entry are various obstacles that stop a [[Peer]] from beginning [[Product]]ion.

These natural and artificial scarcities of access to [[Physical Sources]] restrict [[Competition]].

Competition approaches perfection as barriers to entry approach zero.

But, since [[Profit]] approaches zero as [[Competition]] approaches perfection, and since for-profit businesses measure their success according to the profit they extract, some barriers to entry must remain for Capitalism to continue.

These hindrances can also be thought of as a sort of http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Price_support.